The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 November is 7,961 (921.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 November, there were 1,063 new confirmed cases (123.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 November, there were 854 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 24% ( 209 extra cases).
